Location Type

                                                                                  Last Updated On: 17-06-2022


Chapter 1 Location Type


Table of contents


1.1 Adding location types

1.2 Updating location types

1.3 Disabling a location type

1.4 FAQs



Once the environment is set up successfully, the next step is to feed location information. The location hierarchy of any country/context must be defined beforehand. On the basis of location hierarchy, appropriate types need to be created and then the locations can be added.

Firstly, let us understand the term ‘Location Type’. It can be defined as the divisional grouping of a particular geographical region. For example, administrative divisions such as Country, State, Province, etc and other divisions such as ASHA area, ANM area, etc. Each of these divisions along with their level should be added to MEDPlat as a location type. The divisions and their levels can be best demonstrated using a location tree.  

For illustrative purposes, let’s say that MEDPlat needs to be implemented in India. To do this a location tree should be created as shown. (Fig 1.1)

Fig 1.1 Location tree example                                                         


As shown in the above figure, three location hierarchies i.e., Level 1: Country > Level 2: State > Level 3: District, are the location types. They need to be added to MEDPlat first before adding the locations. 

MEDPlat allows you to add any location type relevant to your context. In brief, it is necessary for MEDPlat to recognize the location hierarchy of the country. 

Adding location information to MEDPlat involves 2 steps:

Step 1: Defining and adding appropriate location types and their levels in the system. It is covered in this chapter.

Step 2: Adding locations under desired location types. It is covered in Chapter Locations.

In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding location types, updating them and disabling them will be covered.  

1.1 Adding location types

The first step before creating a location is to add all the location types in MEDPlat. In this section, we will see how to add location types.

To add a location type, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Location Type’, and the following screen will appear


  • Click on visible on the top-right corner to add a new location type, you will see the following screen



  • Enter the type* of location. It is a shortcode for the location type. For example, ‘s’ for State. [Mandatory] 


  • Enter the name* of location type. For example, Country, State, etc. [Mandatory] 


  • Enter the level* of location type. ‘Level’ describes the position at which the type occurs in the location hierarchy. E.g., Country has level 1, State/Province has level 2, etc. [Mandatory] 


  • Is SOH Enable? 


  • Click on , you will see a notification and the location type will be added. 

Similarly, add all the location types that are relevant to the context.

1.2 Updating location types

To update a location type, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Location Type’ > Click on the Edit icon under the “Actions” column for the respective location type. The screen will open as shown below

  • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , and the location type will be updated.

1.3 Disabling a location type

If any location type is currently not in use, then you may want to disable it.

To disable a location type, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Location Type’ > click on icon for the respective location type, the screen will appear as shown below

  • Click on Mark as inactive, and the location type will be disabled.

1.4 FAQs


Frequently Asked Questions

What is the meaning of level in location type?

A level of a location type is a number that defines the position of the location type in a location hierarchy.   

For example, a country has level 1, a state has level 2, etc. 

Can we enter multiple location types with the same level?

Yes, you can add multiple location types with the same level. 



Locations

                                                                                   Last Updated On: 22-06-2022


Chapter 2 Locations


Table of contents


1.1 Adding locations

1.2 Updating locations

1.3 FAQs


MEDPlat has a dedicated feature named ‘Locations’ to add the location information belonging to context/country or any geographical region. Location is termed as a particular place or a region that can be categorized into a specific type. Thus, each location is associated with a location type. For example, Gujarat is associated with location type ‘state’.

Adding location information to MEDPlat involves 2 steps:

Step 1: Defining and adding appropriate location types and their levels in the system. It is covered in Chapter Location Type.

Step 2: Adding locations under desired location types. It is covered in this chapter.

It is recommended to read the Chapter 1 Location type before creating locations.


Once the location hierarchy has been created and all the related location types have been added, the next step is to add locations to the system. All locations should be added in a hierarchical manner i.e., Country > State > District >, etc.

The MEDPlat support team adds the location for type ‘Country’. Once the country is added successfully, then you can add all the remaining locations.

In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding locations, and updating them will be covered. 

1.1 Adding locations


To add a location, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Locations’, and the following screen will appear

As seen in the above screenshot, the country location has been added by the support team. Now, the next location type in the hierarchy is the state.


  • Select your country name from the drop-down available in the filter, e.g., India > click on , all locations available under "India" will appear as shown below


  • Click on , and the following screen will open.


  • Select the location type for which you wish to add the location from the drop-down i.e., State


  • Enter the location name in any language e.g., गुजरात. The name entered here will be used everywhere throughout MEDPlat.


  • Enter the English name of your location e.g., Gujarat


  • Enter the LGD Code of your location. It is a unique code for each local government body of India. To get more information, please visit https://lgdirectory.gov.in/


  • Enter the MDDS Code of your location.


NOTE: Please ensure that all the above fields are entered correctly as we cannot delete/disable any added location.



  • Click on , and the location will be added.

Similarly, you can add all the locations under different location types. 


NOTE: You must ensure to select the appropriate location from the filter while adding locations. For example, If you want to add a new district under Gujarat, then select Country -> India, State -> Gujarat and then add a new location under it.


1.2 Updating locations

To update a location, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Locations’ > Select an appropriate location from the filter and click on , all the available locations under the selected will appear as shown below


  • Click on the Edit icon under the “Actions” column. The screen will open as shown below

  • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , and the location type will be updated.

1.3 FAQs


Frequently Asked Questions

What to do if the location type for which the location is to be added doesn’t appear in the drop-down?

If the location type does not appear in the drop-down, then visit the ‘Location Type’ feature > search for the relevant location type. If it does not appear in the list then you need to add it. If it appears in the list then verify that it is active.

Can I add multiple locations with the same name, hierarchy and location type?

No, MEDPLat does not allow you to add multiple locations with the same name and hierarchy. 

Can I add the location name in any preferred language?

Yes, you can add the location in any language of your choice.

Can I delete or disable any available location?

No, MEDPlat does not allow you to delete a location or disable it.







Role and Users

  Last Updated On: 29-06-2022

Medplat has different features in web and mobile applications. For these features, we will require different users for web and mobile applications. Each user must be associated with a role according to the responsibilities of that user. It is mandatory to create a role before creating the user. A role can be associated with a particular location type where a user will be providing services. There is a varied set of roles depending on the country/context.

In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding roles, updating/deactivating a role and assigning features to a role will be covered.

1.1 Adding a new role

To add a new role, follow the steps given below:

  • Navigate to Admin > Role > Click on to add a new role and the following screen will open



  • Enter the Role Name e.g., ANM  [Mandatory]

 

  • Location: Select the location type where the user of this role will be providing the services e.g., ANM user will be providing services at the sub-center level. So, for the ANM role, we will add a subcenter under location. 


  • Max position: Enter the maximum no. of users that you want to create for this role at a particular location e.g., 1 - This means that only 1 ANM user will be created at a particular subcenter. It is recommended that we mention this count so that only required users are created at a particular location.


  • Mandatory Field: If we require the below information to be collected from the user while adding a new user, then it must be marked as true.

  • Email: If marked as true, then the email must be entered while creating a new user. 

  • Contact Number: If marked as true, then the Contact Number must be entered while creating a new user.

 

  • Can Manage Role: Select the role(s) that will be managed by this role. Here the list of already added roles will be shown. While creating a new role, if we want to provide rights to the new role to manage the existing roles, then we can select one or more roles from the list shown e.g., while adding an Admin role, if we want the admin user to manage the ANM role, then we must select the ANM role from here. This means that the admin user will be able to manage the ANM role and also add or update users of the ANM role.


  • Self-Manage: It’s recommended to mark self manage as true while creating a new role so that newly created role can add or update their own role and also add or update the users e.g., while adding an admin role, if we mark this option as true, then all users of the admin role will be able to manage the admin role and also add or update users of the admin role.


  • Health Infrastructure Type: Select the health infrastructure type. We can associate a role to a particular health infrastructure type where the users of this role will be providing the services e.g., we can associate district type of health infrastructures with a district MO role. So, while creating a user of a district MO, we will be able to associate a particular district hospital with this user.


  • Category: Select the category.


  • Click on and the role will be added successfully and listed in the list of roles.


The next step is to assign the features to the newly added role. Only the assigned features will be visible when a user with this role logs in to the application.

1.2 Assigning features to the role

Following sections detail the steps to assign features to the role.


  • Navigate to Admin > Role > Click on any role from the list of roles as shown below or type the role name in the search box for which the feature is to be assigned  



       


  • Select the role > you will see the ‘assigned feature’ and ‘actions’ column on the right side.


  • Click on , and you will see the following screen




  • Select one or more features from the dropdown


  • Click on , features will be assigned to this role and it will be visible in the ‘assigned feature’ column.


Similarly, you can add more features to any role.


1.2.1 Actions


Following are the actions associated with this feature


Delete the assigned feature


  • Select the role > you will see the ‘assigned feature’ and ‘actions’ column on the right side.





  • click on the delete icon and the feature will be removed from this role


Search a feature


  • To search a feature in the assigned features list, type into the search box and your searched result will appear in the list.

1.3 Updating a role

  • On the right side, search for the desired role from the list of roles > click on the edit icon 


  • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , and the role will be updated.

1.4 Deactivating a role

  • On the right side, search for the desired role from the list of roles > click on the more icon as shown below





  • Click on the ‘Mark as Inactive’ button > a notification appears > Role deactivated.


NOTE: The role that is deactivated can be made visible in the list of roles, by clicking on the ‘Include Inactive’ checkbox in the list of roles. Then, all the inactive roles will also be displayed in the list.


























Chapter 2 Users


User Management is an integral part of MEDplat. There are numerous users are created belonging to different roles based on the services they offer. After role creation, the next step is to create new users for that role. Every user is assigned a role and features on the basis of the role. 

In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding users, and updating/deactivating them will be covered.

2.1 Adding new user

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Users’, and the following screen will appear


  • Click on to start adding the user, and the following screen will open




  • User Role: Select the role of this user from the drop-down list e.g., ANM [Mandatory]


  • Title: Select the title e.g., Mr.


  • First Name: Enter the first name of the user  [Mandatory]


  • Middle Name: Enter the middle name of the user.


  • Last Name: Enter the last name of the user [Mandatory]


  • Gender: Click on any of the radio buttons to select the gender [Mandatory]


  • User Name: Enter the username [Mandatory]


  • Password: Enter the password [Mandatory]


  • Confirm Password: Re-enter the password added in the above password field [Mandatory]


  • CUG Phone Number: Enter the valid phone number of the user.


  • Email: Enter the valid email address of the user.


  • Preferred Language: Select the preferred language [Mandatory]


  • Select Area of Intervention. Select the location according to the location type set while creating the role. This is the location where the user will be performing the assigned tasks or providing services to the beneficiaries. For example, while adding the user of the ANM role, it will be mandatory to select the location up to the sub-center. Click on Add button, and make sure that location is added under the ‘Added Areas’ section


Note: In the same way, we can associate the user with multiple areas of intervention. 


  • Click on to save this user list. Details of this user will be displayed in the list of users.

2.2 Updating a user

To update a user, follow the steps given below.

  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Users’ > On the right side, search/filter the desired user from the list of users > click on the edit icon as shown below 


  • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , and the user will be updated.

2.3 Downloading the list of users


  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Users’ > On the right side, search/filter the desired user from the list of users > Click on icon to download the list of users as a ‘PDF’ File.

OR


  • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Users’ > On the right side, search/filter the desired user from the list of users > Click on icon to download the list of users as an ‘Excel’ File



  

2.4 Deactivating the user



    • On the right side, search/filter the desired user from the list of users > click on the more icon as shown below




    Click on the ‘Mark as Inactive’ button > a notification appears, and the user deactivated.















    Features

    Features refer to the permissions related to each menu item available in MEDPlat. MEDPlat is flexible enough to grant access to any menu item for any individual user or based on their roles.


    NOTE: “Features” lists all the menu items related to the web interface of the MEDPlat application. For the configuration of menu items in the Mobile application, we have a separate feature named “Mobile Menu Management”.

    1.1 Grant access rights to a menu


    Different users have different access rights to the menu items available on MEDPlat web. However, we can configure access to different menu items based on the role as well as individual users. 


    To grant access to a menu item, follow the steps given below.

     

    • Navigate to Admin > click on ‘Features’, the following screen will appear


     


    As highlighted in the screenshot above, on the top-most bar we have all the modules available on the web. The left-side panel contains a list of features available under a selected module. For example, currently, the “FHS” module is selected, and then all features available under FHS, i.e., CFHC Report, etc, will be displayed.


    You need to select features from the left-hand column to assign to “users” or “roles”. When you use a role, everybody under that role will have access to the menu item. Alternatively, you can provide access to individual users regardless of their role. 


    Grant access based on role


    • Select an appropriate feature to be allocated from the left-hand side panel e.g., manage> select role from the Role drop-down e..g, FHW (you can select multiple roles also) > click on , access will be granted, and the role will be added to the list as shown below




     By this method we can give permissions to a particular role.

    Grant access to a user


    • Select an appropriate feature to be allocated from the left-hand side panel e.g., > select user from the User drop-down e..g, John Smith > click on , access will be granted, and the user will be added to the list as shown below




    1.2 Revoke access to a menu 


    Sometimes you may not want the certain role or users making changes to some features on an ongoing basis. So you may revoke access that was granted before.


    To revoke access to a menu item, follow the steps given below.


    • Navigate to Admin > click on ‘Features’ > select an appropriate feature from the left-hand side panel e.g., Manage > click on the delete icon under the “Actions” column for the user/role whose access needs to be revoked as shown below




    The menu item will not be available for access to the user/role.

    Mobile Menu Management is a MEDPlat web feature that allows you to assign the mobile features to different users based on their roles. Each role has been assigned a different set of features based on its tasks and responsibilities. You can also update the mobile menu of any role by adding features or removing a given feature. 


    Refer to the below-given illustration for a better understanding of this feature.



    As shown in the above illustration, a mobile menu for the User role is created and relevant features are added to it. Once ASHA logins into her mobile application, she will be able to view the newly added features.


    NOTE: The admin user who is assigning the features to the mobile role needs to be aware of the correct feature names. 

    1.1 Create a new mobile menu for a role

    In this topic, we will see how to create a new mobile menu for a particular role and assign features to it.


    Example: Create a new mobile menu for the ASHA role and assign the following features.

    1. ASHA FHS
    2. ASHA MY PEOPLE
    3. Library
    4. Work Status
    5. Work log


    • Navigate to Admin > click on ‘Mobile Menu Management’, and the following screen will appear



    You will find a list of existing menu items for different roles.

    • Enter Menu Name as ASHA Menu

    NOTE: Features that are to be assigned to any role must be available and added by the development team. If you do not find the feature in the dropdown, then please contact the administrator for support. 


    It will be added to a table below and also on the mobile screen on the right as shown below 



    Similarly, add all the other required features from the drop-down.


    • Click on button and the menu will be created as shown below.



    Now, perform a refresh(sync) from the home screen of the mobile application or try to re-login in the app to see the added features.

    1.2 Updating mobile menu for a role


    You can update an existing menu by adding new features or deleting a feature from the menu. In some circumstances, there might be some features that are of no use to a particular role. Hence, you can delete those features by updating the menu. You can even add a new role if you wish to have the same mobile menu for them.  


    To update an existing mobile menu, follow the steps given below


    • Navigate to Admin > click on ‘Mobile Menu Management’ > click on the Edit icon of the respective menu as shown below



    Once clicked, the screen will appear as shown below.



    • Update the menu according to your requirement > click on the button and the menu will be updated.


    1.3 Deleting mobile menu for a role


    You can delete the entire menu for any role. 


    To delete the mobile menu for a role, follow the steps given below


    • Navigate to Admin > click on ‘Mobile Menu Management’ > click on the Delete icon of the respective menu as shown below



    Once clicked, you will see a confirmation box as shown below asking you to delete the menu or not.



    • Click on , and the menu will be deleted


    1.4 FAQs


    Frequently Asked Questions

    I am not able to find the feature in the dropdown. What to do?

    1) Ensure that the feature you wish to assign is available and already added by the development team.

    2) Contact the administrator for support.

    I have added the feature from the web app but it does not show on the mobile app. What to do?

    1) Re-check in the web app if the correct feature was assigned or not.

    2) Perform refresh(sync) from your home screen.

    3) Logout from the mobile application and perform login again to see the translation.

    4) Contact the administrator for support.



    Health Facility Mapping

     Last Updated On: 27-04-2023

    Chapter Health Facility Mapping

     

    Table of contents

    1.1 Managing health infra type

    1.2 Adding a health facility

    1.3 Updating a health facility

    1.4 Deleting a health facility


    A health facility is a location where healthcare is provided. Each health facility is associated with a health infra. Health infra is a general term used for all facilities. For example, District hospitals, Medical college hospitals, etc. MEDPlat allows you to add and manage all the facilities available for any context. The health infra associated with the respective facility should be added first before adding the facility.

     

    Adding health facility information to MEDPlat involves 2 steps:

    Step 1: Defining and adding appropriate health infra types.

    Step 2: Adding health facilities under desired health infra.

    In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding health infra, and facilities and managing them will be covered.


    1.1 Managing health infra type

    Adding health infrastructure type

    To add a health infra, follow the steps given below.

    • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Health facility mapping’, and the following screen will appear

    A list of the added facilities will be displayed.

    • Click on and the following screen will open 


    • Click on Add New to add a new infrastructure type and the following screen will open



    • Health Infra Type [Mandatory]: Enter the name of the health infra type.


    • Location type [Mandatory]: Select the location type from the dropdown. This will allow the user to map the health infra type with the location type.


    • Click on Save, health infrastructure type is added successfully.


    To deactivate any health infra type, follow as given below.


    • Click on the more icon as shown below




    • Click on the ‘Mark as Inactive’ button > a notification appears, and the infra type is deactivated.


    1.2 Adding a health facility


    • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Health facility mapping’ > Click on , following screen will appear

    Fig 7.2 Adding health facility


    • Name: Enter the name of the health facility [Mandatory]


    • Name ( In English ): Enter the name of the health facility in English [Mandatory] 


    • Type: Select the type of health infrastructure type from the dropdown. Health facilities are of various types such as PHC, SC, District Hospital, Sub District Hospital etc. According to the type of health infrastructures, facilities, categories and lab tests are orchestrated and configured. [Mandatory]


    • Address: Enter the physical address of the health facility.


    • Postal Code: Enter the postal code of the health facility.


    • Geo Location: Enter the latitude and longitude coordinates of the health facility.


    • No. of Beds: Enter the total number of beds in the health facility.


    • No. of PPE: Enter the total number of PPE ( Personal Protective Equipment ) in the hospital.


    • National Identification Number: NIN number is a unique 10-digit number within India. It’s useful to identify the geographical location of the health facility. For this purpose,  attributes like state, district, taluka, and village codes based on MDDS (Meta Data & data Standards) will be attached to NIN. [Mandatory]


    • Landline Number: Enter the telephone number of the health facility.


    • Mobile Number: Enter the mobile number of the health facility.


    • Email: Enter the email id of the health facility.


    • Contact Person Name: Enter the name of the person who is the point of contact.


    • Contact Number: Enter the contact number


    • State: Select state e.g. Gujarat > Select Region e.g. Ahmedabad Region > Select District e.g. Ahmedabad > Select Block e.g. Daskroi > Select PHC e.g. Aslali > Click on ‘Add Location’, location added in the ‘Added Areas’. Here, the level of location hierarchy options will be determined by the type of health infrastructure. [Mandatory] 


    On the right side of the screen, you will see the following list of facilities available in this health facility. Select all the facilities that are available in this health facility. Based on the selected facility, select or deselect the category and type of lab tests conducted. 


    Fig 7.2 Adding health facility


    • Click on , the health facility will be saved and you will be redirected to the main screen.


    1.3 Updating a health facility



    • Click on Manage > Health Facility Mapping > In ‘Search Health Infrastructures’, Click on the edit icon in any health facility 


    • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , health facility will be updated successfully.



    1.4 Marking inactive a health facility


    In order to mark inactive any health facility, please ensure that there are no users who have been associated with that facility.


    • Click on Manage > Health Facility Mapping > In ‘Search Health Infrastructures’, Click on the icon in any health facility


    NOTE: If there is any user who has been associated with the facility then it cannot be deleted until the association is removed.




    • The system will show the facility as inactive.





    User profile

                                                                                        Last Updated On: 29-07-2022


    Chapter User Profile

    Table of contents


    1.1 Updating your profile

    1.2 Changing the password for your account

    1.3 Logging out of the application

    1.4 FAQs



    This chapter will help you to update your profile details i.e., change the preferred language for the application, change the password for your account, etc. Your profile also provides you the leverage to change the reporting language in the application.



    1.1 Updating your profile


    You can change the language of the MEDPlat mobile application as well as the language of reporting according to your preference. To view the application in your preferred language, you need to perform the following:


    1) Provide the translation for each label

    You can translate the labels using Manage translations feature. For more information, refer to the Chapter Manage translations. 


    2) Set the language under your profile 

    It is explained below.


    To set the language, follow the steps given below.


    • Click on your profile name on the top right-hand corner of the dashboard > click on as shown below



    Once you click on the “Update profile” button, the following screen will open.



    • Select language from the Preferred Language dropdown > select report viewing language from Report Preferred Language dropdown > click on and the language for the mobile application will be updated.


    NOTE: Please ensure that the language translation of each label is provided, then only you will be able to view the application in your preferred language.

    You need to re-login into your mobile application in order to view the application in your preferred language.

    1.2 Changing the password for your account


    MEDPlat facilitates you to change the password for your account if you wish to for security reasons.  


    To change the password for your account, follow the steps given below.


    • Click on your profile name on the top right-hand corner of the dashboard > click on as shown below



    Once you click on the “Change Password” button, the following screen will open.



    • Enter your current password in the Old Password field


    • Enter the new password that you wish to set in the New Password field


    NOTE: New password should not be the same as the Old password and it must be of minimum 8 characters.


    Once you enter the password in the New Password field, you will see a box below it that shows the password strength. For example, if the newly entered password is weak then you will see the following



    Below the box, you will see suggestions to improve the strength of your password. Update your password according to the suggestions. 


    • Re-enter the new password in the Confirm Password field


    • Click on and you will see a notification saying “Password changed successfully”


    1.3 Logging out of the application


    To log out of the application, follow the steps given below.


    • Click on your profile name on the top right-hand corner of the dashboard > click on as shown below



    You will be logged out of the MEDPlat web application and redirected to the login screen.  

    1.4 FAQs




    Frequently Asked Questions

    What are the password requirements?

    A password must be of minimum 8 characters. For setting a strong password, it should contain at least one lowercase letter, one uppercase letter, one number and one special character.

    For example, Abcd@123 

    I am not able to change the language of the mobile application. What to do?

    Ensure that all the labels available in the mobile application have been translated and then the language under your profile has been set. Try to re-login into the mobile application and then check again. If the language still doesn’t change, then contact the administrator.

    I cannot find the ‘Hindi’ language in the preferred language dropdown. What to do?

    If you are unable to find the language in the preferred language dropdown then please contact your administrator.

    I am not able to change the password of my account. What to do?

    1) Make sure the new password has minimum 8 characters and the new password should not be the same as the old password. 

    2) Check if your internet connection is available or not.

    3) Contact your administrator.

    Chapter 2 Locations


    Table of contents


    1.1 Adding locations

    1.2 Updating locations

    1.3 FAQs


    MEDPlat has a dedicated feature named ‘Locations’ to add the location information belonging to context/country or any geographical region. Location is termed as a particular place or a region that can be categorized into a specific type. Thus, each location is associated with a location type. For example, Gujarat is associated with location type ‘state’.

    Adding location information to MEDPlat involves 2 steps:

    Step 1: Defining and adding appropriate location types and their levels in the system. It is covered in Chapter Location Type.

    Step 2: Adding locations under desired location types. It is covered in this chapter.

    It is recommended to read the Chapter 1 Location type before creating locations.


    Once the location hierarchy has been created and all the related location types have been added, the next step is to add locations to the system. All locations should be added in a hierarchical manner i.e., Country > State > District >, etc.

    The MEDPlat support team adds the location for type ‘Country’. Once the country is added successfully, then you can add all the remaining locations.

    In the upcoming topics of this chapter, adding locations, and updating them will be covered. 

    1.1 Adding locations


    To add a location, follow the steps given below.

    • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Locations’, and the following screen will appear

    As seen in the above screenshot, the country location has been added by the support team. Now, the next location type in the hierarchy is the state.


    • Select your country name from the drop-down available in the filter, e.g., India > click on , all locations available under "India" will appear as shown below


    • Click on , and the following screen will open.


    • Select the location type for which you wish to add the location from the drop-down i.e., State


    • Enter the location name in any language e.g., गुजरात. The name entered here will be used everywhere throughout MEDPlat.


    • Enter the English name of your location e.g., Gujarat


    • Enter the LGD Code of your location. It is a unique code for each local government body of India. To get more information, please visit https://lgdirectory.gov.in/


    • Enter the MDDS Code of your location.


    NOTE: Please ensure that all the above fields are entered correctly as we cannot delete/disable any added location.



    • Click on , and the location will be added.

    Similarly, you can add all the locations under different location types. 


    NOTE: You must ensure to select the appropriate location from the filter while adding locations. For example, If you want to add a new district under Gujarat, then select Country -> India, State -> Gujarat and then add a new location under it.


    1.2 Updating locations

    To update a location, follow the steps given below.

    • Navigate to Manage > click on ‘Locations’ > Select an appropriate location from the filter and click on , all the available locations under the selected will appear as shown below


    • Click on the Edit icon under the “Actions” column. The screen will open as shown below

    • Update the field according to your requirements > click on , and the location type will be updated.

    1.3 FAQs


    Frequently Asked Questions

    What to do if the location type for which the location is to be added doesn’t appear in the drop-down?

    If the location type does not appear in the drop-down, then visit the ‘Location Type’ feature > search for the relevant location type. If it does not appear in the list then you need to add it. If it appears in the list then verify that it is active.

    Can I add multiple locations with the same name, hierarchy and location type?

    No, MEDPLat does not allow you to add multiple locations with the same name and hierarchy. 

    Can I add the location name in any preferred language?

    Yes, you can add the location in any language of your choice.

    Can I delete or disable any available location?

    No, MEDPlat does not allow you to delete a location or disable it.
